						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 45, Śubhakṛit, Āśvayuja, puṇṇime, Sōmavāra, Sōma-grahaṇa,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1122 September 17 Sunday,</hi> not Monday, when there was a lunar eclipse. It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> ruling in <hi rend="bold">Kalyāṇa</hi> and mentions <hi rend="bold">Kumāra Tailapadēva</hi> as ruling over <hi rend="bold">Sindavāḍi thousand.</hi> The latter's feudatory Trailōkyama • • • • is stated to have been ruling <hi rend="bold">Pombuḷige seventy-three</hi> and some other divisions (names lost). As Tailapadēva's gift, some grant of land was made on the date.</p>						

						<p>First face.</p>						

						</summary>
